Build this module with:

$ perl Makefile.PL
$ make
$ make test
(Try "prove -vb t/*" instead of "make test" for verbose output.)

Have a look at lib/XSTest.pm. If has a list of (optionally) exported
function names.

Your code goes in XSTest.xs.

It doesn't hurt to have a clone of the perl source repo:

  git clone http://perl5.git.perl.org/perl.git


Relevant documentation:

perlxstut.pod
perlxs.pod
perlapi.pod

More advanced or specialized:
perlhack.pod
perlhacktips.pod
perlhacktut.pod
perlguts.pod
perlintern.pod
perlinterp.pod
perlcall.pod
perlsource.pod
